            <bug_when>2007-05-23 11:48:27 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>This bug seems to affect Gecko browsers only.

To reproduce this bug use a splitpane with a tree widget inside and populate the tree with a long tree folder label.
Change the size of the splitpane to force the scrollbar to show up. Shorten the tree folder label via a button click.
Gecko does not adjust the scrollbar nor hides it when the scrollbar is no longer needed. IE6/7 and Opera are acting right.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
